ROUTE_APP_OFFLINE

static final int ROUTE_APP_OFFLINE
Constant used in routing response which indicates that the route cannot be calculated because the application is offline. This would happen in the case of online routing when the application was turned to offline mode.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ROUTE_INTERNET_IS_TURNED_OFF

static final int ROUTE_INTERNET_IS_TURNED_OFF
Constant used in routing response which indicates that the route cannot be calculated because the internet is turned off. This would happen in the case of online routing when the client turns off the internet connection on the device.

See Also:
Constant Field Values
Method Detail

onRouteCalculationCompleted

void onRouteCalculationCompleted(int statusMessage,
                                 int routeDistance,
                                 int routeEta,
                                 boolean thisRouteIsComplete,
                                 int id)
Called when the route calculation is completed. In case of long routes, the route is computed partially, so the callback will be called 2 times: first time with the thisRouteIsComplete = false, then with thisRouteIsComplete = true.

Parameters:
statusMessage - - status message 600 means the route was calculated

Possible values are: ROUTE_SUCCESS, ROUTE_NO_RESULTS_FOUND, ROUTE_IDENTICAL_ALTERNATIVE, ROUTE_SAME_START_AND_DESTINATION,ROUTE_INVALID_START, ROUTE_INVALID_DESTINATION,ROUTE_INTERNAL_ERROR, ROUTE_CANNOT_BE_CALCULATED,ROUTE_INVALID_VIA_POINT, ROUTE_APP_OFFLINE, ROUTE_INTERNET_IS_TURNED_OFF

routeDistance - route length in meters
routeEta - estimated time for the route in seconds
thisRouteIsComplete -

- true, if the route is complete.

id - unique id of the route

onAllRoutesCompleted

void onAllRoutesCompleted()
Called when the calculation of all routes are completed.

onServerLikeRouteCalculationCompleted

void onServerLikeRouteCalculationCompleted(int status)
Called when completing the calculation of a route by onboard request.

Parameters:
status - Possible values are: ROUTE_SUCCESS, ROUTE_NO_RESULTS_FOUND, ROUTE_IDENTICAL_ALTERNATIVE, ROUTE_SAME_START_AND_DESTINATION,ROUTE_INVALID_START, ROUTE_INVALID_DESTINATION,ROUTE_INTERNAL_ERROR, ROUTE_CANNOT_BE_CALCULATED,ROUTE_INVALID_VIA_POINT, ROUTE_APP_OFFLINE, ROUTE_INTERNET_IS_TURNED_OFF

onOnlineRouteComputationHanging

void onOnlineRouteComputationHanging(int timeSinceTheHangingBehaviorStarted)
Called when an online route computation appears to be hanging.

Parameters:
timeSinceTheHangingBehaviorStarted - the total wait time in seconds since the hanging behavior started
